com.paydiant.android.ui.service.transaction

Class CancelTransactionListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.ui.service.transaction.CancelTransactionListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICancelTransactionListener

    public class CancelTransactionListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements ICancelTransactionListener
    This class provides an empty implementation for ICancelTransactionListener. Any classes that wants to use only a subset of the listener methods can override the relevant methods and use it as the interface implementation. 

     CancelTransactionListenerAdapter cancelTransactionListenerAdapter = new CancelTransactionListenerAdapter() {
 
    @Override
    public void onCancelTransactionSuccess() {
    }
 
    @Override
    public void onCancelTransactionError(PaydiantException e) {
    }
 };
 iCancelTransactionService.setCancelTransactionListener(cancelTransactionListenerAdapter);
    Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.
